replies.body:
> [{quoted}](name=Kjraider,realm=NA,application-id=3ErqAdtq,discussion-id=7sO5RzAR,comment-id=000e,timestamp=2019-03-14T02:40:43.682+0000)
>
> Mages, especially mobile mages, are in an amazing(dare I say OP) place in general. You take a look at most elo's and top/mid(duh) and even support win/pick rates, and mages are well represented compared to ad/tanky variants in most cases. Mage items are dirt cheap, give great stats, and ultimately lead to most of them being able to 100 to 0 in a combo or less. Mage power creep is a problem all over the map, and I'd love to see it addressed in general.

Blatantly untrue.  Go to any of the league statistic sites and you'll see that AD champions are very overrepresented in all lanes.  There isn't a single AP champion on the top 5 most overall played champions, and the only AP champions in the top 10 more played are {{champion:517}} and {{champion:25}}  who both have inflated pick rates caused by Sylas being the newest champion release and Morgana being a new rework release.

The most common picks in each position are:
top: {{champion:92}} 
jng: {{champion:64}} 
mid: {{champion:238}}
sup:{{champion:412}} 
bot: {{champion:81}}

Where are these overrepresented AP champions?
And before you go "oh 'magi' you must be a biased mage main" you'll see that I actually play all classes if you check my match history, and my highest mastery champ is an AD juggernaut.  {{champion:83}} 
My display name is referring to historical magi, as in Persian wisemen.
